INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (8,19,'Maryellen Bashioum','marynote@aol.com','','98.69.221.53','2012-08-24 13:30:14','2012-08-24 17:30:14','Hi Elyse,  I grew up in Somerville (born 1938).  Our house was beside the rr tracks (not there how).  I loved the trains, especially when they would stop and the cattle and sheep were bawling--and the smell.  The people were wonderful and I knew all the neighbors.  Would visit a old single lady for afternoon tea and we would chat.  Then Somerville went through a very bad time with drugs and many homes started to deteriorate.  My sister and I went back to help our parents move and how wonderful it was to see the positive changes with young families moving in and fixing the houses.  I am hoping to get back there and see for myself and do some genealogy work.  I got married at St. Catherine\'s--hope it is still there.  Thank you for your website and good luck with it.  Maryellen McKelvey Bashioum',0,'1','','',3,0);
