INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (209,1581,'Ron Newman','rnewman@thecia.net','','108.1.141.86','2012-08-20 12:00:29','2012-08-20 16:00:29','The original Steve\'s was on Elm Street, where Posto pizzeria is today.   After Steve\'s closed, its building was torn down and replaced with the current one, built originally for Carberry\'s Bakery.\n\nAfter Steve Herrell sold it to Joey Crugnale, the chain rapidly expanded both regionally and eventually nationally.  They also began packaging ice cream for supermarket sale.  Then the chain collapsed and disappeared -- and I don\'t really know why.\n\nThe very last Steve\'s-branded store, to my knowledge, was at the east end of the Quincy Market building in Boston.   The store still exists but has been renamed to Sprinkles.\n\nMeanwhile, Steve Herrell got back into the ice cream business with a Northampton store called Herrell\'s.  This too became a regional chain for a while, but one by one all of his Boston-area stores have closed.',0,'1','','',0,0);
