INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (227,4,'2012-05-03 14:34:30','2012-05-03 14:34:30','I absolutely love Indian food, but I hate the heavy, overly full feeling I get often after eating it. So when Dosa Temple opened at 447 Somerville Ave., I was really excited to try this exclusively vegetarian restaurant that promised a lighter, but still satisfying meal.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/DT-inside.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-229\" title=\"DT inside\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/DT-inside-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" /></a>Don\'t let the outside (or inside) of Dosa Temple fool you, while it might not look like much, the food is flavorful and fresh. I had prompt, friendly service when dining there on a recent weeknight, which goes a long way in my book. I love cooking, so great service is critically important to any dining out experience that I have.\r\n\r\nI ordered the Spring Dosa, which was a crepe stuffed with cabbage, carrot, potato and onion, rolled and sliced. The vegetables were cooked perfectly, just slightly crunchy and not mushy at all. I especially loved the liberal use of cilantro. My husband ordered the Temple Special Masala Dosa, which was a rolled and sliced crepe with spicy chutney, sauteed onion, tomato and potato. Both dishes were very flavorful, but still simple and light.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/DT-spring-vegetable.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-230\" title=\"DT spring vegetable\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/DT-spring-vegetable-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" /></a>We really enjoyed the sauces that came on the side, especially the coconut one, and the soup was tasty as well. While the portions were large, they were actually very appropriately sized for a meal made up mostly of vegetables.\r\n\r\nDosa Temple has an extensive menu with something for everyone and I know I\'ll be back to try some of the appetizers, more dosas and a curry or two!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://dosatemple.com/Site2/home.html\">Dosa Temple</a>\r\n447 Somerville Ave.\r\n617-764-3152, 617-764-3153\r\n\r\n[google-map-sc]','Dosa Temple Offers Simple, Tasty Vegetarian Fare','','publish','open','open','','dosa-temple-offers-simple-tasty-vegetarian-fare','','','2012-10-15 16:00:36','2012-10-15 20:00:36','',0,'http://www.somervillebeat.com/?p=227',0,'post','',3);
