INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (331,3,'2012-05-06 14:14:05','2012-05-06 14:14:05','Hi! This is Mike, the self-styled master of this webzone. Since the site is a work in progress, I think it would be a good idea to have a page for technical mumbo jumbo, bug reports, etcetera.\n\n<h3>5.30.12 Adaptive Images, Facebookness & more</h3>\n<p>Been pretty busy with work + bbqing, but finally got around to adding/fixing some more stuff on the site. Here\'s what\'s been happening recently:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Implemented <a href=\"http://adaptive-images.com/details.htm\">Adaptive Images</a> to try and speed up pageload on mobile phones (and just fool around with it in general)</li>\n<li>Added a jQuery lightbox functionality for gallery posts going forward (old uploads are too big to retrofit)</li>\n<li>Changed some of the social links on the front page, now you can \"like\" us without leaving the comfort of the homepage!</li>\n<li>Added FB like and send buttons to posts</li>\n<li>Swithed up the \"THE\" in the header image, it was bugging me. Designer problems.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And if anyone knows how to line up that annoying Twitter button on the entries, let me know. It\'s in an iframe and is getting some vertical-align screwiness from somewhere, but I haven\'t been able to track it down.</p>\n\n\n<h3>Cross Browser</h3>\n<p>We\'ve tested the Beat on the latest versions of Chrome, Safari, Firefox and Internet Explorer (8 + 9). The site works, but isn\'t very pretty in older versions of IE. If you run into anything I missed, give a shout to <a href=\"mailto://admin@somervillebeat.com\">admin@somervillebeat.com</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>Mobile</h3>\nReading the Beat on your phone or tablet is easy thanks to the magic of <a title=\"Thanks Ethan!\" href=\"http://www.alistapart.com/articles/responsive-web-design/\">responsive design</a>—reformatting the webpage based on your device width.\n\nIf you\'re on an iThing (iPhone, iPod, iPad) you can add a shortcut to the Beat like this:\n<h3>1. Tap shortcut icon</h3>\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/shortcut-icon.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-335\" title=\"shortcut-icon\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/shortcut-icon-300x187.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"187\" /></a>\n<h3>2. Tap \"Add to home screen\"</h3>\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/shortcutt-add.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-336\" title=\"shortcutt-add\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/shortcutt-add-159x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"159\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n<h3>3. Give it a name</h3>\nIt defaults to \"Somerville B\", but I like to just call it \"Beat\".\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/shortcut-add.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-334\" title=\"shortcut-add\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/shortcut-add-159x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"159\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n<h3>4. Ta-da!</h3>\nNow a link to the Beat will appear with your apps.\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/shortcut-homescreen.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-333\" title=\"shortcut-homescreen\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/shortcut-homescreen-159x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"159\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n','Tech talk','','publish','open','open','','tech','','','2012-05-06 14:14:05','2012-05-06 14:14:05','',0,'http://www.somervillebeat.com/?page_id=331',0,'page','',4);
