INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (357,4,'2012-05-14 07:00:13','2012-05-14 11:00:13','I was waiting until after Mother\'s Day to post this because we were lucky enough to score some great presents at <a href=\"http://www.somervillebeat.com/things-to-do/somerville-open-studios-5-4-5-6/\">Open Studios</a> this year. Now that the holiday has come and gone, I want to share what we loved so much that we couldn\'t leave it behind.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/OS-candlesticks.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-360\" title=\"OS ring\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/OS-candlesticks-1024x682.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWe got this ring, made by Teeru Bihani of <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/bluehelixdesigns\">Blue Helix Designs</a>, for Mike\'s mom at the <a href=\"http://www.somervillebeat.com/?p=283\">Armory</a>. She loves big, beautiful rings and this one fit the bill perfectly!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/IMG_1452.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-361\" title=\"OS candlesticks\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/IMG_1452-682x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"960\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThese candlesticks were made by <a href=\"http://juliepeckceramics.com/\">Julie Peck Ceramics</a>, whose studio we stumbled on while walking around town. She had so many gorgeous creations on display that it was difficult to choose which to buy, but I knew my mom would love these.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/OS-poster.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-358\" title=\"OS poster\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/OS-poster-1024x905.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"565\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWe picked up this <a href=\"http://thebrianhart.com/\">Brian Hart</a> poster at <a href=\"http://www.somervillebeat.com/features/open-studios-fringe-union/\">Fringe Union</a>, our first stop during Open Studios weekend. It was printed by Mike Dacey of <a href=\"http://repeatpress.com/\">Repeat Press</a> (who also works out of Fringe) and I just love the colors.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/OS-art1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-359\" title=\"OS art\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/OS-art1-1024x682.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" /></a>\r\n\r\nI first saw <a href=\"http://vernonstreet.com/artists/lubeck.html\">Suzanne Lubeck\'s</a> art at the <a href=\"http://www.somervillebeat.com/?p=297\">Vernon Street Studios</a> a couple of years ago and I\'ve been kicking myself for not buying any ever since. So when we found her again this year, I kew we couldn\'t leave without a piece. We selected this mixed media because we live in Prospect Hill and love it!\r\n\r\n<em>What did you buy at Open Studios? Anything you left behind that you can\'t stop thinking about?</em>','Open Studios: What We Bought','','publish','open','open','','open-studios-what-we-bought','','','2012-10-15 16:23:21','2012-10-15 20:23:21','',0,'http://www.somervillebeat.com/?p=357',0,'post','',1);
