INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1018,4,'2012-06-28 07:00:56','2012-06-28 11:00:56','One of my favorite things to do on the weekends in the summer is head to the <a href=\"http://unionsquaremain.org/food/farmers-market/\">Union Square Farmers Market</a>. I usually hit the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/SomervilleWinterFarmersMarket\">Somerville Winter Farmers Market</a> in the Armory on Highland Ave. when it\'s open, but there\'s something really special about picking out fresh fruits and veggies, fish and sweet treats outdoors on a warm summer morning.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Greens.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-1026\" title=\"Greens\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Greens.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"560\" height=\"373\" /></a></p>\r\nOn a recent visit, greens of all kinds looked vibrant and ready for salads, sautés and soups. We picked up some fresh bok choy, one of my favorite vegetables, which I like to wilt in a pan and drizzle with soy sauce so it caramelizes a bit. Then I sprinkle on some sesame seeds and serve!\r\n\r\nI also got some of Jordan Bros.\' remaining fresh catch, swordfish. I\'ve tried nearly every type of fish and shellfish they offer and have always been really impressed by the quality and freshness of the food.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/7Ate9.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-1021\" title=\"7Ate9\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/7Ate9.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"560\" height=\"352\" /></a></p>\r\nIggy\'s Bread is always a tempting booth, with its crusty yet soft whole wheat sourdough bread and yummy bagels. <a href=\"http://www.somervillebeat.com/food/593/a-sweet-new-venture-for-culinary-cruisers/\">Culinary Cruisers</a> was selling kombucha on tap and its Ocean Ave Pops, while many area farms had goods like spring strawberries, beautiful eggs and local maple syrup.\r\n\r\nIf you\'re looking for something sweet, there\'s usually a booth or two of chocolate or pastries. And this year Journeyman is selling ice cream, perfect for a hot summer day.\r\n\r\n<em>What\'s your favorite booth at the farmers market? What\'s the most delicious thing you\'ve ever made with farmers market ingredients? See you there this weekend!</em>\r\n<h3>Details</h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://unionsquaremain.org/food/farmers-market/\">Union Square Farmers Market\r\n</a>Saturdays 9 a.m.-1 p.m., June 2-November 17\r\nUnion Square Plaza\r\n\r\nP.S. Don\'t forget about the new <a href=\"http://www.somervillebeat.com/?p=988\">Swirl &amp; Slice Market</a> in Union Square on Thursdays from 5 p.m.-8 p.m. from June 14-September 20! And there\'s also the <a href=\"http://www.somervillebeat.com/food/638/somerville-farmers-markets/\">Davis Square Farmers Market</a>, which runs on Wednesdays from noon-6 p.m. from May 23-November 21.\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"file\"]','Somerville Summer: A Trip to the Union Square Farmers Market','','publish','open','open','','somerville-summer-a-trip-to-the-union-square-farmers-market','','','2012-10-15 16:13:48','2012-10-15 20:13:48','',0,'http://www.somervillebeat.com/?p=1018',0,'post','',8);
