an upscale vegan eatery that is sure to leave both vegetarians and carnivores satisfied. And looking ahead, don\'t forget to get your <a href=\"http://somervillebeat.com/things-to-do/2411/harvest-fest-a-celebration-of-somerville-for-the-day/\">Harvest Fest</a> tickets for next Saturday\'s event or sign up to volunteer and get in free for a few hours!</em>','Weekend 10.19-10.21: Pre-Halloween Events','','inherit','open','open','','2497-autosave','','','2012-10-18 16:39:26','2012-10-18 20:39:26','',2497,'http://somervillebeat.com/things-to-do/2503/2497-autosave/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2505,4,'2012-10-21 15:12:47','2012-10-21 19:12:47','In the recent survey I conducted, I found out that Beat readers really like the weekend things to do posts. Also in the survey, someone suggested including more ideas on things to do in Somerville during the week. That inspired me to find out what\'s happening around town regularly that could spice up a ho-hum mid-week night. This isn\'t an exhaustive list, so if you have any fun events to share, please leave them in the comments. Thanks to whoever suggested this post topic and to everyone who filled out the survey!\n\n<!--more-->\n<h3>Sunday</h3>\n<a href=\"http://bullmccabesboston.com/index.htm\">Bull McCabe\'s</a>\nFootball on seven screens and 50-cent wings from 1 p.m.-8 p.m.\n366A Somerville Ave.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.burren.com/index.html\">The Burren</a>\nGrunge Brunch from 10 a.m.-3 p.m.\n247 Elm St.\n\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/TOS-HK-Soup.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-808\" title=\"TOS HK Soup\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/TOS-HK-Soup-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" /></a><a href=\"http://highlandkitchen.com\">Highland Kitchen</a>\nBrunch with live music 11 a.m.-2:30 p.m.\nLive music at 10 p.m. (no cover)\n150 Highland Ave.\n<em>(Soup from Highland Kitchen at the <a href=\"http://www.somervillebeat.com/food/796/taste-of-somerville-serves-up-delicious-dishes/\">Taste of Somerville</a> pictured at right.)\n</em>\n<a href=\"http://www.johnnyds.com/\">Johnny D\'s</a>\nJazz brunch, food 8:30 a.m.-2:30 p.m., live music at 9:45 a.m.\nOpen blues jam from 4 p.m.-7 p.m., no cover\n17 Holland St.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.joshuatreesomerville.com/\">Joshua Tree</a>\nBrunch with $3 mimosas\n256 Elm St.\n\n<a href=\"http://magounssaloon.com/\">Olde Magoun\'s Saloon</a>\nGerman-inspired Sunday roasts (September and October)\n518 Medford St.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.orleansrestaurant.com/\">Orleans</a>\nGame night (various board games)\n65 Holland St.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.thirstyscholarpub.com/\">Thirsty Scholar Pub</a>\nTrivia Night at 8 p.m.\n70 Beacon St.\n<h3>Monday</h3>\n<a href=\"http://bullmccabesboston.com/index.htm\">Bull McCabe\'s</a>\nStump! team trivia at 8 p.m.\n366A Somerville Ave.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.burren.com/index.html\">The Burren</a>\nThe 5K Bur-Run at 6:45 p.m.\n247 Elm St.\n\n<a href=\"http://highlandkitchen.com\">Highland Kitchen</a>\nFried chicken and tiki drinks\n150 Highland Ave.\n\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/The-Indo.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-936\" title=\"The Indo\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/The-Indo-300x210.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"210\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.theindo.com/\">The Independent</a>\n$1 oysters on Monday nights if you sit at the bar\n76 Union Square\n\n<a href=\"http://www.johnnyds.com/\">Johnny D\'s</a>\nTeam trivia at 8:30 p.m.\n$1.50 hot dogs from 6 p.m.-10 p.m.\n17 Holland St.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.joshuatreesomerville.com/\">Joshua Tree</a>\nLive music by Chris Ferrara\n256 Elm St.\n\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/TOS-Kickass-Cupcakes.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-811\" title=\"TOS Kickass Cupcakes\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/TOS-Kickass-Cupcakes-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.kickasscupcakes.com\">Kickass Cupcakes</a>\nCupcake cocktail hour on the last Monday of every month from 5 p.m.-8 p.m.\n378 Highland Ave.\n\n<a href=\"http://magounssaloon.com/\">Olde Magoun\'s Saloon</a>\n25-cent wings during Monday Night Football\n518 Medford St.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.orleansrestaurant.com/\">Orleans</a>\nPasta night ($14.95 gets you a bowl of pasta and a house salad)\n$5 appetizers and $1 oysters Monday-Friday from 3 p.m.-7 p.m.\n65 Holland St.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.paslounge.com/\">P.A.\'s Lounge</a>\nOpen Mic Night\n345 Somerville Ave.\n\n<a href=\"http://sallyobriensbar.com/\">Sally O\'Brien\'s</a>\nCheapshots Comedy Club Open Mike at 7:30 p.m.\nMarley Mondays with The Duppy Conquerors at 10 p.m.\n335 Somerville Ave.\n<h3>Tuesday</h3>\n<a href=\"http://www.burren.com/index.html\">The Burren</a>\nOpen mike, sign up at 6:30 p.m., show starts at 8 p.m.\n247 Elm St.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.eastsomervillemainstreets.org/\">East Somerville\n</a>First Tuesdays: A monthly after-hours free event open to the public where you can sample fare from the East Broadway business district.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/Flatbread-Somerville/115976338415327?sk=wall\">Flatbread Pizza</a>\nFundraiser night, buy a pizza and help a good cause at 5 p.m.\n45 Day St.\n\n<a href=\"http://highlandkitchen.com\">Highland Kitchen</a>\nSpelling bee on the first Tuesday of the month at 10 p.m.\n150 Highland Ave.\n\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/TOS-Magouns.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-814\" title=\"TOS Magoun\'s\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/TOS-Magouns-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a><a href=\"http://magounssaloon.com/\">Olde Magoun\'s Saloon</a>\nTeam trivia from 8:30 p.m.-11:30 p.m.\n518 Medford St.\n<em>(Dishes from Olde Magoun\'s Saloon at the <a href=\"http://www.somervillebeat.com/food/796/taste-of-somerville-serves-up-delicious-dishes/\">Taste of Somerville</a> pictured at right.)\n</em>\n<a href=\"http://onthehilltavern.com/\">On the Hill Tavern</a>\nStump! trivia\n499 Broadway\n\n<a href=\"http://www.orleansrestaurant.com/\">Orleans</a>\nTaco night (choose from six different varieties)\n$5 appetizers and $1 oysters Monday-Friday from 3 p.m.-7 p.m.\n65 Holland St.\n\n<a href=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/TOS-PJ-Ryans.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-821\" title=\"TOS PJ Ryan\'s\" src=\"http://somervillebeat.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/TOS-PJ-Ryans-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.pjryans.com/index.html\">PJ Ryan\'s</a>\nPub Quiz at 10 p.m.\n239 Holland St.\n<em>(Dishes from PJ Ryan\'s at the <a href=\"http://www.somervillebeat.com/food/796/taste-of-somerville-serves-up-delicious-dishes/\">Taste of Somerville</a> pictured at right.)\n</em>\n<h3>Wednesday</h3>\n<a href=\"http://www.burren.com/index.html\">The Burren</a>\nPub quiz from 8 p.m.-10 p.m.\nComedy night at 10 p.m.\n247 Elm St.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.cantinalamexicana.com/\">Cantina La Mexicana</a>\nFree salsa with introductory lesson from 7 p.m.-9 p.m.\n247 Washington St.\n\n<a href=\"http://highlandkitchen.com\">Highland Kitchen</a>\nKaraoke at 10 p.m.\n150 Highland Ave.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.joshuatreesomerville.com/\">Joshua Tree</a>\nGeeks who drink trivia from 8:30-10:30\n256 Elm St.\n\n<a href=\"http://magounssaloon.com/\">Olde Magoun\'s Saloon</a>\nOktoberfest menu from September 5-October 31, 5 p.m.-11 p.m.\n518 Medford St.\n\n<a href=\"http://onthehilltavern.com/index.html\">On the Hill Tavern</a>\nSports trivia\n499 Broadway\n\n<a href=\"http://www.orleansrestaurant.com/\">Orleans</a>\nTrivia at 8 p.m.\n$5 appetizers and $1 oysters Monday-Friday from 3 p.m.-7 p.m.\n65 Holland St.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.precinctbar.com/index.php\">Precinct</a>\n3penny open mike, no cover\n70 Union Square\n\n<a href=\"http://sallyobriensbar.com/\">Sally O\'Brien\'s</a>\nFree poker with lots of prizes at 8 p.m.\n335 Somerville Ave.\n<h3>Thursday</h3>\n<a href=\"http://www.burren.com/index.html\">The Burren</a>\nL80\'s night (women get in free and $2 beer, $3 shots for everyone)\n247 Elm St.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.caseyssomerville.com/\">Casey\'s</a>\nSomerville Road Runners 4.13 Miler at 7:15 p.m.\n173 Broadway\n\n<a href=\"http://www.joshua