ur of the historic site. There is a suggested $5 donation for adults (seniors and children are free) and costumes are encouraged!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/445105248864029/\">Day of the Dead at Taza Chocolate Factory Store:</a> Head to <a href=\"http://somervillebeat.com/things-to-do/1301/a-taste-of-taza-chocolates-unique-sweets/\">Taza Chocolate</a> (561 Windsor St.) on Sunday from 1 p.m.-5 p.m. for the store\'s annual Day of the Dead celebration. There will be a taco truck, live mariachi band, free samples from Slumbrew, Q\'s Nuts and Chive Sustainable Events. Taza will also provide some special Day of the Dead treats and will have T-shirts for sale. And anyone wearing a Day of the Dead costume to the event will receive 10% off a factory store purchase.\r\n\r\n<em>P.S. Have you entered to win two tickets to Cuisine en Locale\'s <a href=\"http://somervillebeat.com/things-to-do/2516/giveaway-win-two-tickets-to-once-de-los-muertos-ii/\">ONCE de los Muertos</a> dinner and dancing fiesta taking place next Friday, November 2 at Arts at the Armory (191 Highland Ave.)? Tell us your best Halloween costume in the <a href=\"http://somervillebeat.com/things-to-do/2516/giveaway-win-two-tickets-to-once-de-los-muertos-ii/\">comments on this post</a> or <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SomervilleBeat\">Tweet</a> us (or do both) and you\'ll be entered to win two tickets to this festive event!</em>','Weekend 10.26-10.28: Festive Fall Fun','','publish','open','open','','weekend-10-26-10-28-festive-fall-fun','','','2012-10-26 07:57:00','2012-10-26 11:57:00','',0,'http://somervillebeat.com/?p=2524',0,'post','',0);
